  "description": "A lighter evening recipe designed to feel comforting without becoming heavy or starch-dense. Vegetable Appam with Stew brings a distinct structure, seasoning pattern, and grain-legume balance to the table.",
  "preparation": "",
  "cooking_steps": [
    "Cook the appam one at a time in an appachatti, swirling the batter for lacy edges and a thicker center.",
    "For the stew, soften onion, ginger, chilli, and curry leaves in oil over medium heat for 2 minutes.",
    "Add the vegetable, peas, salt, and 180 ml water; cover and cook on medium-low heat for 7 minutes until almost tender.",
    "Add coconut milk and simmer gently on low heat for 4 minutes. Serve the stew with hot appam."
  ],
